[{"id": "9aee8847-573f-4bcd-8954-cfb756b3af37", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "USER: kelly is sitting alone at lunch with her headphones on. a boy named craig is intermittently throwing food at her.\nASSISTANT: The canteen buzzed at a frequency her Bose headphones couldn't quite cancel. She had them on anyway\u2014the pressure around her ears was almost as good as the silence. Almost. Her left hand tapped against her thigh in a pattern of four, right hand busy turning pages of the packet she wasn't actually reading.\n\nSomething hit her shoulder.\n\nA pea. Rolled down her baggy shirt and landed on the table. She brushed it away without looking up.\n\nAnother one. This time it bounced off her headphone cup and skittered across the laminate surface. Her hand stopped tapping. She kept her eyes on the packet, but the words had stopped making sense two minutes ago.\n\nThere. Movement in her peripheral vision. A boy two tables away\u2014Craig, she thought his name was Craig\u2014grinning at someone beside him, hand dipped into his tray. His arm moved in that casual way boys' arms moved when they were being pricks.\n\nShe turned the page she hadn't read.\n\nA chip landed in her hair. She felt it settle against her scalp, greasy and warm. Her fingers twitched. The urge to reach up and grab it warred with the stronger urge to not give him the satisfaction. Her leg started bouncing under the table instead, heel hitting the floor in quick staccato bursts.\n\nThe chip slid down behind her ear and caught in the collar of her shirt.\n\nShe didn't move. Didn't look. Just breathed and tapped and waited for lunch to end.", "embedding": [-0.05827460065484047, -0.01875140890479088, 0.07721786946058273, -0.03289375826716423, 0.03918352723121643, -0.04169173538684845, 0.14992345869541168, -0.004451182205229998, 0.022867128252983093, 0.007941344752907753, 0.07845132797956467, 0.009409911930561066, 0.005389849655330181, -0.00284280302003026, -0.06828217208385468, -0.0052389963530004025, 0.059